data.distributionNotes: E Australia from NE Queensland through W New South Wales and Victoria, including King I and Tasmania. Distribution is primarily continuous within some catchments but dicontinuous or poorly known in others. Extinct in the Adelaide Hills and Mount Lofty Ranges in South Australia and may be extinct in various catchments throughout the rest of their distribution (Hawke et al., 2019). Introduced to E Kangaroo I.
